Hacksaw
KomperaMy point wasn't that the items I had were counter to the new rarities, it was that there didn't seem to be any real sense to how the new rarities were assigned. There's no particular reason to make 2 parts of a 6 part blade rare, while the remaining parts are non-rare. There's no real reason to make one laser pointer rare and the other three non-rare.

In the real world, the number of full sets of a given collection is defined by the number of items for which there is the fewest in existence. (for instance, they can sell a million blue, green and red laser pointers, but if there's only 10 000 orange laser pointers then there can only be 10 000 full sets of laser pointers). For collectors, these rare items become far more valuable than most of the other components of the set, where those other components are often times not worth much on their own, but can be giving much greater value when sold in bundle with the rare component.

For a video game there is no maximum number of full sets that can be made amongst all players of the game, but the concept around the rare component still applies. How "value" is assigned to a given item, however, depends on the game in question (such as in an MMO where items can be bartered or sold, where the current possessor of the rare component can demand more other items and/or in-game currency for the component).

For this game, the "value" of the item ultimately boils down to how much time and/or money a given player is willing to spend on this game to complete their sets for the icons, titles, Twinoid points, et cetra. Likely MT is betting on some people's competitive nature or OCD'ness to spend months or years of their life constantly playing this game until they can get everything, hoping that they'll spend budget points on skipping the timer, buying in-game items, using the teacher's assistants and anything else they might add in the future, and in spending budget on these features they're hoping these players will be more willing to spend real life cash on more budget to play more games and use more features.
